***Calls On Security Agencies To Prosecute Perpetrators ENUGU- Ikeoha Campaign Organization has raised alarm over harassment and intimidation melted on his supporters during the last Peoples’s Democratic Party (PDP) Ward Congress in Enugu. Addressing a press conference in Enugu on Friday, the Director General of Ikeoha Campaign Organization, Hon Charles Ogbo Asogwa said the harassment is in the bid to intimidate and stop the gubernatorial ambition of Former Senate Deputy President, Senator Ike Ekweremadu. -Advertisement- He recalled “we had formerly raised alarm over the rising political intolerance and highhandedness on our supporters even before the Ward Congress and In particular we also called the attention of the nation to the appointment of known deadly thugs and cultists into state and local government offices all in the bid to intimidate and stop Distinguished Senator Ike Ekweremadu,” Showing the footage of the attack to Journalists on the screen, Hon Asogwa expressed worry that despite reporting the previous incident, the trend took yet another dangerous dimension during the 30th April 2022 Ward Congress when our supporters were brutally attacked again as they shot sporadically causing stampede in the area ,” he said “The primary purpose of government is the security of the lives and property of the people. It therefore beats the imagination that all these political violence have continued unabated. “Recall that our principal and number one gubernatorial aspirant in the 2013 governorship race, Senator Ike Ekweremadu has severally called on the national and state leadership of the PDP to ensure a free fair , transparent and therefore credible process so that the whoever emerges PDP’s flag bearer for any of the political office will be embraced by all,” he said He thereby called on the security agencies to arrest and prosecute all perpetrators of violence in Enugu state. POLL “We also call on all lovers of peace and democracy to join hands to persuade the authorities to take the necessary and decisive steps to arrest this growing culture of political violence, cultism and banditry to ensure a peaceful primary and 2023 general election in Enugu state,” he said